%% Diagram: How backpressure propagates backward through a pipe chain
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Src as ReadableStream
    participant TX as TransformStream
    participant Sink as WritableStream

    Note over Src,Sink: Steady state. Chunks flow downstream.
    Src->>TX: enqueue chunk
    TX->>Sink: write chunk
    Sink-->>TX: writer ready resolves
    TX-->>Src: pull called again

    Note over Src,Sink: Sink slows down e.g. disk I/O
    Src->>TX: enqueue chunk
    TX->>Sink: write chunk
    Sink-->>TX: writer ready PENDING
    Note right of TX: TX queue fills. Its desiredSize -> 0.
    TX-->>Src: stops calling pull
    Note left of Src: Source MUST check controller desiredSize before next enqueue.
    Src->>Src: skip enqueue and retry later

    Note over Src,Sink: Sink drains
    Sink-->>TX: writer ready resolves
    TX->>Sink: queued write
    TX-->>Src: pull resumes
    Src->>TX: enqueue chunk
